## Blocked — API-level Monitors (DO NOT CREATE YET)

> **2026-07-17 (T0.5 loops)** — Kuma runs on Seko-VPN, which is the Headscale control
> server, not a tailnet client. Every URL below is gated by `import vpn_only` in
> `roles/caddy/templates/Caddyfile.j2`; a public request from Seko-VPN gets Caddy's
> **403 before it ever reaches the backend** (confirmed by curl from the Seko-VPN box).
> Creating these monitors today with `accepted_statuscodes` tuned for the backend
> would read "UP" via the 403 regardless of whether the app is actually alive — a
> false-positive that hides the exact incident they're meant to catch (Plane frontend
> 200 / API 500, 2026-07-17). **Do not create these in the Kuma UI until the routing
> blocker is resolved** — see `~/work/infra/Seko-VPN/docs/09-uptime-kuma-monitors.md`
> for the two proposed fixes and the human gate required before either ships.

